{
  "stem": "1895.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I actually opened it up, took out the bill of lading.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And on the bill of lading I saw clearly marked Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So from Blizyn, we went to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And Auschwitz began this new era for me.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Saul Mincberg remained in the camp.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was one of the 50 that remained to clean up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know the Germans never left-- left abruptly everything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were very thorough, well-organized, very efficient.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They left 50 people to clean up and to dismantle whatever they needed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So Saul was among those, but I met him later.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We came into Auschwitz in the summer of 1944.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I think it was either the end of June or in July.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a new saga began for me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Because of certain connections and of a friend of mine who found a-- a boyhood friend of his working in the sauna, which was some kind of a privileged job in Auschwitz, we were given the opportunity to go on a work kommando that was-- that worked in a close proximity to the arrival ramp where the people came into Auschwitz arrived.",
      "word_count": 62
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I worked on the arrival ramp for several months.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And for several months, daily I witnessed the many, many, many transports that came in from all over Europe, transports that came in from Western Europe, Holland, Belgium, France, and also from the Lodz ghetto, which was being emptied out at that time.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And most of them came in from Hungary.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was all in the period when I worked at the-- The summer of '44?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Summer of '44.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "500,000.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
